sql:
SELECT a.program, AVG(a.entrance_exam_score) AS average_entrance_score
FROM admissions a
GROUP BY a.program;

SELECT COUNT(admission_id) AS total_accepted_students
FROM admissions
WHERE admission_status = 'accepted';

external_knowledge:
- Admission category refers to the way students are admitted to a program (e.g., JOSAA/CSAB-2020); 
- Active admission rounds refer to the admission rounds that are currently open or in progress; 
- Students with disabilities are those who have reported having any disability.
